Evian Tournament in France Is Designated Fifth Women’s Golf Major by LPGA

-- B y   M i c h a e l   B u t e a u
-- 
2011-07-20T14:19:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-20/evian-tournament-in-france-is-designated-fifth-women-s-golf-major-by-lpga.html
The Evian tournament in  France  was
added as the fifth major event in women’s golf by the LPGA tour.  The designation, announced in a news release, takes effect
in September 2013. The championship will be played on a
redesigned Evian Golf Club course, in Evian-Les-Bains, near Mont
Blanc.  The other majors on the tour are the Kraft Nabisco
Championship, the LPGA Championship, the U.S. Women’s Open and
the Women’s  British Open .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Larry Siddons at 
 lsiddons@bloomberg.net  